---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout'
---

<BaseLayout title='Privacy Policy - TutorialsPoint'>
	<main class='max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12'>
		<div class='prose prose-lg max-w-none'>
			<h1 class='text-4xl font-bold mb-8'>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p class='text-gray-600 mb-8'>Last updated: December 13, 2024</p>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>1. Introduction</h2>
				<p>
					Welcome to TutorialsPoint. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect
					your personal information when you use our website (tutorialspoint.org) or our services.
					By using our site, you agree to this policy.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>2. Information We Collect</h2>
				<p>We collect information to improve your experience and provide better services:</p>
				<ul class='list-disc pl-6'>
					<li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Name, email, and other contact information.</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, and device information.
					</li>
					<li><strong>Behavioral Data:</strong> Interactions, course progress, and preferences.</li>
					<li><strong>Cookies:</strong> To personalize your experience and track preferences.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
				<p>Your data helps us:</p>
				<ul class='list-disc pl-6'>
					<li>Deliver and maintain our services.</li>
					<li>Enhance user experience and website functionality.</li>
					<li>Send notifications and updates (e.g., for new tutorials or courses).</li>
					<li>Provide customer support and technical assistance.</li>
					<li>Monitor and improve our services.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>4. Data Security</h2>
				<p>
					We prioritize your data security using industry-standard practices. While we strive for
					maximum protection, no method of online transmission is completely secure.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>5. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
				<p>
					We use cookies to enhance site functionality and user experience. You can manage cookie
					preferences through your browser settings.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
				<p>We may share limited data with trusted third-party services for purposes like:</p>
				<ul class='list-disc pl-6'>
					<li>Analytics to understand website usage (e.g., Google Analytics).</li>
					<li>Email notifications and course updates.</li>
					<li>Payment processing (if applicable).</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>7. Your Rights</h2>
				<p>You have the following rights regarding your data:</p>
				<ul class='list-disc pl-6'>
					<li>Access, update, or delete your personal information.</li>
					<li>Restrict data processing or withdraw consent.</li>
					<li>Request a copy of your stored data.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
				<p>
					Our services are not directed at individuals under 13. We do not knowingly collect data
					from children.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
				<p>
					We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. The updated policy will be posted here
					with a new "Last Updated" date.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class='mb-8'>
				<h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>10. Contact Us</h2>
				<p>If you have any questions or concerns about this policy, contact us at:</p>
				<ul class='list-disc pl-6'>
					<li>Email: <a href='mailto:privacy@tutorialspoint.org'>privacy@tutorialspoint.org</a></li>
					<li>Contact page: <a href='/contact'>tutorialspoint.org/contact</a></li>
				</ul>
			</section>
		</div>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
